nd lingual practices, as well as religious and literary activities of the medieval Jews of Egypt.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aJewszEgyptxHistoryyTo 1500. 7aHISTORY / Jewish.2bisacsh  aAyyubids.  aCairo Geniza.  aDhimma.  aEgypt.  aFatimids.  aHebrew poetry.  aIslam.  aJewish-Muslim relations.  aJudaism.  aJudeo-Arabic literature.  aMamluks.  aMedieval.  aMiddle Ages.  aMoses Maimonides.  aancient.  aantiquity.  aantisemitism.  aculture.  acustoms.  aeconomy.  afamily life.  ageography.  ahistory.  alanguage.  alaw.  amarriage.  aminorities.  amishnah.  apolitics.  areligious practice.  aself-government.1 aCohen, Mark R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrenkel, Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrenkel, Miriam, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrenkel, Yehoshua, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGoldberg, Jessica, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIlan, Tal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMazor, Amir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuss-Fishbane, Elisha, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWagner, Esther-Miriam, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYagur, Moshe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYahalom, Joseph, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aZinger, Oded, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074321008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe 